snippet.title: Joe Biden is ‘self-imploding’
snippet.description:
Filmmaker Ami Horowitz says Joe Biden is “self-imploding”.

Donald Trump is leading President Joe Biden in 11 of 12 national surveys taken after the presidential debate.

“Trump is able to control himself and not go nuts on this,” Mr Horowitz told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.

“He is letting this all play out.

“When your opponent is just self-imploding, you just let it happen and don’t interfere.”

snippet.title: Jen Psaki Breaks Down What Would Happen if Biden Were to Step Down from Running
snippet.description:

snippet.title: "Doomed to fail" | LBC's best callers this week
snippet.description:
00:00 | James O'Brien caller Suresh brands the Tories as 'desperate and quite hypocritical' over claims of Labour's win being a 'supermajority'. 

04:54 | Caller Glen is a regular listener to Nick Ferrari's show, telling the presenter that he usually speaks 'a lot of sense' but on the issue of Keir Starmer taking Friday evenings off, Glen labels Ferrari's stance as 'nonsense'. 

06:40 | Tom Swarbrick caller John is a baby boomer and in response to criticism of the party, he says he agrees with rumours that 'pensioners will be taxed more' under Keir Starmer. 

10:21 | 42-year-old first time voter Alex tells Nick Ferrari that he's 'embarrassed' that 'racist' Reform UK came second to Labour in many places.

12:21 | Matthew Wright argues with caller David, who believes the Labour Party is 'doomed to fail' with their 'idealistic policies'.

Listen to the full show on Global Player: https://app.af.globalplayer.com/Br0x/LBCYouTubeListenLive

snippet.title: The Existential Dread of False Ceilings
snippet.description:
Watch my next video right now about the lost technology of a utopian town!
https://nebula.tv/videos/stewarthicks-lost-technology-of-a-failed-utopian-city
Get Nebula using my link for 40% off an annual subscription: https://go.nebula.tv/stewarthicks

__Special Thanks__
Evan Montgomery — co-producer, filming, and editing

__Description__
Why do false ceilings get such a bad rap? From oppressive office spaces to iconic movie scenes, these ubiquitous fixtures seem to symbolize everything wrong with corporate life. But are they really that terrible? In this video, we explore the history and evolution of drop ceilings, from their introduction in the 1930s to their widespread use in modern architecture. Discover how they solve practical issues like heat and noise while keeping unsightly building systems out of view. Join our discussion about the surprising engineering marvels of drop ceilings and let’s challenge their reputation. It’s time to rethink the ceiling above your head.


__Membership__
Join this channel to get access to perks:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCYAm24PkejQR2xMgJgn7xwg/join

__About the Channel__
Architecture with Stewart is a YouTube journey exploring architecture’s deep and enduring stories in all their bewildering glory. Weekly videos and occasional live events breakdown a wide range of topics related to the built environment in order to increase their general understanding and advocate their importance in shaping the world we inhabit.

__About Me__
Stewart Hicks is an architectural design educator that leads studios and lecture courses as an Associate Professor in the School of Architecture at the University of Illinois at Chicago. He also serves as an Associate Dean in the College of Architecture, Design, and the Arts and is the co-founder of the practice Design With Company. His work has earned awards such as the Architecture Record Design Vanguard Award or the Young Architect’s Forum Award and has been featured in exhibitions such as the Chicago Architecture Biennial and Design Miami, as well as at the V&A Museum and Tate Modern in London. His writings can be found in the co-authored book Misguided Tactics for Propriety Calibration, published with the Graham Foundation, as well as essays in MONU magazine, the AIA Journal Manifest, Log, bracket, and the guest-edited issue of MAS Context on the topic of character architecture.

__Contact__
FOLLOW me on instagram: @stewart_hicks & @designwithco
Design With Company: https://designwith.co
University of Illinois at Chicago School of Architecture: https://arch.uic.edu/

__Special Thanks__
Stock video and imagery provided by Getty Images, Storyblocks, and Shutterstock.
Music provided by Epidemic Sound

snippet.title: Chicago’s NASCAR Race is a Marvel of Physics
snippet.description:
Use code stewarthicks at the link below to get an exclusive 60% off an annual Incogni plan: https://incogni.com/stewarthicks

__Special Thanks__
+ Evan Montgomery — coproducer, filming, editing

__Description__
This video explores the intricate planning and design that transformed the heart of Chicago into a 2.2-mile race track for NASCAR's Next Gen cars. It comes from a combination of cutting-edge technology, historical motorsport legacy, and urban planning to create this unique racing experience. From the car itself to the layout and surface of the streets, everything works together to make the event possible. There’s another key development that helped make it possible as well. Sim racing, specifically iRacing who created a digital twin of the course to design and test the conditions, ensuring the best possible layout for both racers and spectators. Then Chicago made real-world modifications to the streets to address safety, performance, and spectator experience, based on data from virtual races.

snippet.title: Why 3D Printing Buildings Leads to Problems
snippet.description:
Head to Henson Shaving https://bit.ly/39XCoKw, pick out a razor, add 100 pack of blades, use code: STEWARTHICKS and the blades are FREE!

__Special Thanks__
Institute for Architectural Science and Technology (IAST) https://www.iast.uk/: technical animations
Evan Montgomery: co producer, editor

__Description__
In this video, we explore the hurdles of 3D printed houses and the strange, sometimes impractical results. Companies worldwide are striving to make this technology scalable, affordable, sustainable, and appealing to those who prefer traditional homes. If successful, it could revolutionize how we design and build structures. But will it?

snippet.title: Why Every City Wants a Wrigley Field
snippet.description:
Head to https://www.cutsclothing.com and use code STEWARTHICKS at checkout for 20% off your entire order!

__Special Thanks__
Evan Montgomery — coproduction, filming, editing

__Description__
Let’s take a closer look at Wrigley Field, home of the Chicago Cubs, as it sets an example for stadium urban development. Unlike so many stadiums, which are isolated amidst vast parking lots or separated from their communities by highways, Wrigley Field delivers as good neighbor in a mixed-use context. Its integration into the surrounding community ensures the area will remain a hub of activity, regardless if there is a game going or not.

As cities across the United States begin to reimagine their approach to stadium development, Wrigley Field offers invaluable insights. The video covers the challenges and successes of embedding such a massive sports venue within an urban fabric, highlighting the incremental changes and careful planning that have allowed Wrigley Field to become an inseparable part of its neighborhood. We contrast this with the experiences of other stadiums, including Guaranteed Rate Field, and the evolving dynamics of public funding for stadiums, stadium neighborhood integration, and the economic impact of stadiums on their local communities.

Here’s what other cities can learn from Chicago's experience. 

__Tags__
Wrigley Field, Urban Development, Mixed-use Development, Stadium Economic Impact, Public Funding Sports Arenas, Chicago Stadiums, Urban Planning Sports Facilities, Stadium Community Benefits

snippet.title: The Most Useless Megaprojects in the World
snippet.description:
From an empty airport used as a go-karting track, to man-made islands that are sinking back     into the sea. And from two fully functional nuclear power plants that were never switched on to the largest abandoned amusement park in the world. This is part 4 of our most useless megaprojects series.

snippet.title: How Central Park Was Created Entirely By Design and Not By Nature | Architectural Digest
snippet.description:
Today Michael Wyetzner of Michielli + Wyetzner Architects joins AD in New York for an in-depth walking tour of Central Park. Everything in Central Park got there by considered choice, not by nature, and the park as we know it today is the result of a design competition held in the 1850s. From hidden through-roads to its calming bodies of water, join Michael as he walks you through why Central Park is the best-designed city park in the world.

Director: Hiatt Woods
Director of Photography: Eric Brouse
Editor: Tristen Rogers
Host: Michael Wyetzner

snippet.description:

snippet.title: How 5 Bridges Transformed New York City | Architectural Digest
snippet.description:
Today Michael Wyetzner of Michielli + Wyetzner Architects joins AD for an in-depth look at how bridges transformed New York City into the thriving metropolis we know today. Once upon a time, ferries were the only way to travel between New York’s five boroughs but thanks to the construction of major bridges, like The Brooklyn Bridge and The George Washington Bridge, the city became connected. Join Michael for a closer look at how five bridges helped shape NYC into the bustling city we know today.  

00:40 The Brooklyn Bridge
05:05 The Hellgate Bridge
08:25 Macombs Dam Bridge
11:18 The High Bridge
14:07 The George Washington Bridge

snippet.title: How to See Venice in A Day
snippet.description:
Our Best Venice Tours: https://thetourguy.com/tours/venice 

We give you the formula of how to have an epic day in Venice Italy. All the practical advice on the new tourist tax in Venice, where to eat in Venice, how to get around Venice and how to visit Venice in a Day Guide. #venice #venezia #veniceitaly 

Venice is a city unlike any other, with stunning architecture, winding canals, and a rich history. If you only have one day to explore this magical city, don't worry - we've got you covered. 

In this video, we'll take you on a tour of the top sights and hidden gems of Venice, from St. Mark's Basilica and the Doge's Palace to the Rialto Bridge and the Fish Market. Along the way, we'll also share our tips for getting around the city by boat and enjoying the best food and drink that Venice has to offer. Whether you're traveling solo or with a group, this video will help you make the most of your day in Venice. So, sit back, relax, and get ready for a day of adventure in one of the most beautiful cities in the world. 

With our "How to Visit Venice in a Day" guide, you'll make the most of your limited time in this unforgettable city. Don't miss out on the chance to experience the magic of Venice. 

Quick Subscribe to our Channel: https://bit.ly/3iicLnG

Welcome to our comprehensive guide to making the most out of your trip to Barcelona! In this video, we'll dive into essential travel tips, insider knowledge, and must-see attractions to ensure your visit to this vibrant city is unforgettable.

From navigating the bustling streets to indulging in mouthwatering Catalan cuisine, we've got you covered with practical advice and local insights. Whether you're a first-time visitor or a seasoned traveler, there's something for everyone in Barcelona.

Join us as we explore iconic landmarks like the Sagrada Familia and Park Güell, uncover hidden gems tucked away in charming neighborhoods, and sample the best tapas and paella the city has to offer.

Get ready to immerse yourself in Barcelona's rich history, culture, and breathtaking architecture. With our tips, you'll be able to create memories that will last a lifetime in this enchanting Mediterranean paradise.

snippet.title: Barcelona’s Gothic Quarter | 10-STOP WALKING TOUR
snippet.description:
Discover MUST-VISIT & HIDDEN sites in Barcelona’s famous Gothic Quarter. Come with me on this walking tour on the Gothic Quarter. I'll show you the famous Plaça Nova, Pont del Bisbe, the Roman temple, Plaça Sant Felipe Neri, Plaça del Rei, the Jewish Quarter, Plaça San Jaume and the Port de Mar. Venga, let’s go! 🥝

MORE ABOUT THIS VIDEO 😃 
⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯

Barcelona’s Gothic Quarter can be really confusing! So many winding streets, so many tourists, so much to see! But it’s actually quite a small area, and it’s one of the most magical collections of 13-15th century buildings in the world. 

And did you know that Barcelona’s Gothic Quarter is actually built on the remains of a 2,000 year old Roman settlement?

Also, not everything is as it seems in the Gothic Quarter. There are lots of secrets in this part of the city, but you have to know where to find them. I will show you!

To sum it up, the Gothic Quarter is a place you really need to visit. It’s also called the Barrio Gótico in Spanish and the Barri Gòtic in Catalan.

In this video I take you to 10 of the must-see sites in the Gothic Quarter. These are places we visit and you’ll learn about on Devour Tour’s Tapas, Taverns & History Tour. 

At each stop in the video, I give you some information behind the history of the area, and also a little Google marker with the name of the street or square so you can find it yourself.

So, where do we visit?

1. Plaça Nova - where the entry point to the Roman town was
2. Carrer del Paradís - where there is an amazing Roman temple
3. Behind the Cathedral - where you can see lots of hidden symbols
4. General Archive of the Crown of Aragon
5. Plaça del Rei - did Columbus stand on these steps?
6. Pont del Bisbe - the most photographed site in all of Barcelona… but it’s not as old as it seems!
7. Jewish Quarter (El Call) - a fascinating little tangle of streets with a long history
8. Plaça Sant Felipe Neri - my favourite square in the city… and with a dark secret
9. Plaça Sant Jaume - the perfect place to decode the Catalan independence issue
10. Pont de Mar - the exit point of the old Roman city!

MORE INFO ABOUT THIS VIDEO 😃
⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
Barcelona is an amazing place to eat! But here’s the thing - it can also be hard to eat well in Barcelona because it’s so touristy. There are just so many options, and lots of them literally are tourist traps. But happily there are also so many incredible places to eat and delicious things to taste and drink if you just know where to look.

In this video I take you to 10 of my favourite places to eat 10+ incredible bites.  And we visit 3 famous neighbourhoods across the entire video. We go to the Born, the Gothic Quarter and La Barceloneta - three neighbourhoods that you have to visit, and we’ll eat delicious food in each!

And a number of places are places we visit on Devour Tour’s food tours - including our Tastes & Traditions of Barcelona Food Tour and our Tapas, Taverns & History Food Tour

Also, once you’ve watched this, be sure to check out my playlist of Barcelona videos - including my epic 9-stop Barcelona Tapas Crawl.

So, where do we go?
1. Granja Dulcinea for an incredible suizo (chocolate and cream!)
2. Mercado Santa Caterina: We visit Bar Joan for a fry-up breakfast and cava and Antonio Iberics for a fantastic selection of cured meats. Plus, we visit a stall for delicious escalivada.
3. Historic Casa Gispert for a selection of wood-roasted almonds, and chocolate treats
4. Hofmann Pastisseria for an insane marscapone croissant
5. La Campana for delicious turrón and horchata
6. Xarcutería La Pineda for vermouth and a selection of potato chips with Espinaler sauce, cheeses and salt-cured anchovies
7. Bodega La Palma for patatas bravas and red wine
8. Can Paixano for a delicious butifarra sandwich and also a pork loin and cheese sandwhich - all knocked back with their famous cava
9. La Cova Fumada for a bomba (it was invented here!), grilled squid and grilled sardines
10. Can Ramonet for a delicious seafood fideuá and drinking from the porrón!

Salut!

==== WHO ARE WE? ====
Hola, Spain lovers! We're James and Yoly. James is a New Zealander, and Yoly is from Spain. And we both live in Madrid. This channel is all about giving you a local insight into life in Spain, and helping you experience this country like a local when you come to live (or visit!).

snippet.title: Tapas Tour & OLDEST RESTAURANT in The WORLD in Madrid Spain
snippet.description:
On this food adventure, I went to tour the San Miguel Market in Madrid, Spain. This is a great place to visit, sampling some of the best Madrid's market food has to offer. After the market, I went to El Sur to eat gambas, which is shrimp with garlic sauce, and I had some Cuban pulled pork. That pork was my favorite dish there. For dessert, I ate churros with hot chocolate, and this place was incredibly packed, so get ready to wait in line! To end my food day, I went to one of the oldest restaurants in Spain, Botin and it's famous for its roast suckling pig!
 #spain #madrid #spainmadridmarket

snippet.title: Haman-gu & Busan Korea 함안군 & 부산 | VLOG
snippet.description:
Memories with the family and grandparents in 함안 & 부산! Follow along as we eat at a Korean Buffet for 9,000won, explore Haman-gu, a visit to the Relics of Goryeodong in Haman, learning traditional korean instrument and song, eating food samples at Emart Traders, Sauna and Jjimlbang at Hill Spa, and a fun family night at Haeundae Beach.

함안 & 부산에서 가족이랑, 할머니 & 할아버지과 함께한 추억! 9,000원에 무진한상 한식뷔페를 먹고, 함안구 탐방, 함안 고려동 유적지 탐방, 한국 전통 악기와 노래 배우기, 이마트 트레이더스에서 음식 시식, 힐스파에서 사우나와 찜방, 그리고 해운대 해수욕장에서 가족과 함께 즐거운 밤을 보내세요.

Don't forget to subscribe and follow for more!
구독과 팔로우를 잊지 마세요!
-----------------------------

snippet.title: Mukbang at Umeda Osaka Japan | VLOG
snippet.description:
My first time traveling to Japan and stayed 4 days 3 nights at Umeda Osaka! It was a spontaneous trip and filled my stomach with a lot of food! All I did was shop and eat at Japan! I also had the opportunity to experience interacting with deers at Nara Park, eat at two differen revolving sushi such as Kura, visit few spots in Osaka, and shopped all day! Stayed at a great location at Ibis Osaka Umeda Hotel. Follow along as I eat and eat in Osaka, Japan!

처음으로 일본 여행을 떠나 오사카 우메다에서 3박 4일 묵었습니다! 즉흥적으로 다녀온 여행이었는데, 푸짐한 음식으로 배를 든든하게 채웠어요! 제가 한 일은 일본에서 쇼핑하고 먹는 것 뿐이었어요! 나라 공원에서 사슴과의 교감도 경험하고, 쿠라 등 두 가지 회전 초밥에서 식사도 하고, 오사카의 몇 군데를 방문하고, 하루 종일 쇼핑할 기회도 가졌습니다! 이비스 오사카 우메다 호텔에서 좋은 위치에 묵었습니다. 제가 일본 오사카에서 먹고 먹는 모습을 따라해보세요!

Don't forget to subscribe and follow for more!
구독과 팔로우를 잊지 마세요!
-----------------------------

✻ Music/음악 ✻
City Blocks - TrackTribe
Some College - National Sweetheart
Til I Hear'em Say (Instrumental) - NEFFEX
Your Love - Yung Logos
Seasons - Telecasted

GoPro Hero10 Black

snippet.title: Why you MUST visit Arashiyama! Our favourite Kyoto destination!
snippet.description:
Our Kyoto adventure continues despite the overcast skies, which turn out to be perfect for our activities! We trek up to Arashiyama Monkey Park to see the playful monkeys, then wander through the serene bamboo forest. Along the way, we experience the picturesque lake and charming town, sampling some of the delicious sweet treats Kyoto has to offer. Join us for a day full of nature, culture, and delightful moments. Don’t forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more of our Japan journey!

snippet.title: JAPAN Bound with 3 Kids Under 6! Was this a good idea?
snippet.description:
Join our family of five as we embark on an unforgettable adventure to Japan with three kids under six! 
From navigating the airport and entertaining the kids on the flight to settling into our cozy Airbnb and exploring the vibrant Dotonbori district with its colorful food, this video is packed with fun and chaos. Perfect for families planning their own travels or anyone who loves a good travel vlog. Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more of our Japan adventures! New videos each week.

snippet.title: The Claw Machines Are Filled with SANRIO Plush at Round 1!
snippet.description:
Round 1 always has Sanrio plush prizes in their claw machines and UFO catchers! But this time, there are tons of them! We are at Round 1 arcade in Mentor, OH to check out the claw machines and UFO catchers to see what kind of new awesome plush prizes were in stock and to our surprise, they had dozens of claw machines filled with Hello Kitty, Gudetama, Kuroppi, and more Sanrio character plushies! So, of course, we had to try and win them all! In todays claw machine video, we play big claw machines, E claws, Fun Zone claw machines, UFO catchers, and more, to try and win as many of these super cute Sanrio prizes that we can! So join us for another Round 1 arcade adventure as we try and win tons of adorable Sanrio prizes form the claw machines!  

Thank you and keep playing!

snippet.title: Double Claw Machine Win and New Prizes at Round 1
snippet.description:
We are back at Round 1 arcade in Erie, PA to play some claw machines and UFO catchers! This visit we are focusing on some amazing new plush prizes and anime figures! Thank you and keep playing!

snippet.title: We Gave Every Family in a Village a Full Year's Salary
snippet.description:
Help send life-changing cash to the next Ugandan village at http://GiveDirectly.org/beast or by clicking ‘Donate’ above. We’re proud to have helped over 200 families, but there’s plenty more need – so we’re teaming up again to deliver around $1,000 to each of their neighbors in another village just a mile away. Give now and the money will go to more Ugandans in need. Learn more about GiveDirectly’s work at their YouTube page: @givedirectly 



Filmed and Edited by: Dan Mace ( https://www.youtube.com/@DanMace)

snippet.title: We Rebuilt a Village
snippet.description:
Lectric stepped up for these kids again. This company has proven their commitment to building a brighter future time and time again.  Please show them how much you appreciate their incredible support (https://lectricebikes.com). #sponsored

Dora is an exceptional person who has sacrificed so much to give these kids a safe and stable environment. She never rests and is already building 3 more schools. Please follow her on TikTok and Instagram and give her the support and encouragement she deserves.

https://www.tiktok.com/@doramoononyambe
https://www.instagram.com/doramoononyambe 

Contribute directly to Dora here: https://www.gofundme.com/f/feeding-the-children-of-mapapa
or you can click the Donate button, or donate through our website. 100% of donations will go to Dora and the kids.
https://www.beastphilanthropy.org/campaign/we-rebuilt-a-village

When everyone said Beauty’s leg had to be amputated, CURE International (https://cure.org/) said “Hold my ginger beer” and performed a miracle. We could not be more grateful for the exceptional lengths they went to to save her. They do so much to help impoverished children and families around the world and they are one of our favorite partners. Please show them some love.

This is our 5th project with GivePower (​​https://givepower.org/) and we have many more already underway.  We seriously love these people. GivePower delivers solar powered solutions to developing regions across the planet. 


Filmed and Edited by: Dan Mace ( https://www.youtube.com/@DanMace)

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Can I Cook Better Than ChatGPT?
snippet.description:
AI seems to be involved in everything from job applications to "making art." So, we decided to test artificial intelligence in a cooking challenge. My Twitch chat chose the ingredients to make a meal and we asked ChatGPT to make a recipe from those ingredients - my goal was to make something more cohesive and edible than the latest and greatest in artificial intelligence.

The meals were made live on my Twitch stream with my friend,  @aswordbear  , serving as the sous chef for ChatGPT while I represented the human race in our own, homemade version of Food Network's Chopped: Man vs. Machine.

We had to make a delicious and edible recipe from the following ingredients:
- Peanut Butter
- Spicy Pickles
- Pickled Herring in Wine Sauce
- Italian Sausage (Mild)
- Chicken Livers
- Orange Juice
- Sunchokes
- Hot Fudge
- Sweet Chili Sauce
- Pineapple

1:15 The Ingredients

snippet.title: Guessing Star Wars Character Names!
snippet.description:
When I was a kid I loved Star Wars and knew the backstory on so many characters from Luke Skywalker, Han Solo, and Ben Quadinaros. But, with time my knowledge of that far, far, away Galaxy has dwindled and been replaced with The Lord of the Rings. We run through most modern Star Wars media from the Prequels to the Sequels in honor of Star Wars Acolyte dropping this week!

My good friend Coleman (https://www.twitch.tv/colemant16) is a huge Star Wars fan to this day and put together a massive Star Wars character name guessing game that I attempted live on my Twitch channel (along with a Smash or Pass thrown in for good measure)

Enjoy!

snippet.title: Is Return to Moria WORTH Playing In 2024? - Video Essay
snippet.description:
Lord of the Rings: Return to Moria was one of my most anticipated games of last year. Promising to combine survival-crafting gameplay of Valheim with a unique Lord of the Rings twist I was incredibly hopeful and excited for this game.

Now, after 6 months and some time for reflection here is my Return to Moria review. These are my opinions but I hope this video will help you figure out if Return to Moria is worth your money before you buy it.

Chapters:
0:00 Intro
0:52 Part 1: A Royal Welcome
2:11 Part 2: They Call it a Mine...And It's Just Mine?
3:53 Part 3: This Is Not Mine
8:33 Part 4: All That Is Gold Does Not Glitter (Expectations vs. Reality)
12:01 Part 5: Hope For the Future

Return to Moria Dev Blog post and roadmap: https://www.returntomoria.com/news-updates/blog-whats-next

Buy Lord of the Rings: Return to Moria (only if you really, REALLY want to - this doesn't help me at all) https://store.epicgames.com/en-US/p/the-lord-of-the-rings-return-to-moria-f01344

snippet.title: 15 Things I Wish I Knew SOONER About WoW Remix Pandaria
snippet.description:
The WoW Remix Pandaria event can be quite complicated with all of the new temporary features, the odd user interface, the constant buffs and nerfs, and the various different rewards on offer. But in this video we'll go over 15 things that I wish I knew sooner that would have made the entire event much easier to understand, and that will let you progress much smoother and faster to pick up all of those transmogs and mounts.

Become a YouTube member here - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCsxidPdmPXDlsS3rn7arJsA/join
Patreon - https://www.patreon.com/SignsOfKelani
Twitter - https://twitter.com/SignsOfKelani
Discord - https://discord.gg/kelani

00:00 - 15 Things I Wish I Knew Sooner About WoW Remix Pandaria
00:43 - How to unsocket gems faster
01:11 - Your gems are safe
01:31 - Combine gems while moving
01:53 - The best addon for this event
03:12 - You can buy gems to get them faster
04:07 - Put spare gems in your bank
04:33 - Get rested xp on alts early
05:04 - How to power up your alts cloak
06:23 - Power up alts even further
07:08 - Level alts for huge bronze gains

localized.title: 15 Things I Wish I Knew SOONER About WoW Remix Pandaria
localized.description:
The WoW Remix Pandaria event can be quite complicated with all of the new temporary features, the odd user interface, the constant buffs and nerfs, and the various different rewards on offer. But in this video we'll go over 15 things that I wish I knew sooner that would have made the entire event much easier to understand, and that will let you progress much smoother and faster to pick up all of those transmogs and mounts.

Become a YouTube member here - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCsxidPdmPXDlsS3rn7arJsA/join
Patreon - https://www.patreon.com/SignsOfKelani
Twitter - https://twitter.com/SignsOfKelani
Discord - https://discord.gg/kelani

00:00 - 15 Things I Wish I Knew Sooner About WoW Remix Pandaria
00:43 - How to unsocket gems faster
01:11 - Your gems are safe
01:31 - Combine gems while moving
01:53 - The best addon for this event
03:12 - You can buy gems to get them faster
04:07 - Put spare gems in your bank
04:33 - Get rested xp on alts early
05:04 - How to power up your alts cloak
06:23 - Power up alts even further
07:08 - Level alts for huge bronze gains
07:37 - You can teleport to any infinite bazaar
08:14 - Daily quests keep getting better
09:26 - World bosses are totally worth killing
09:56 - The secret to a powerful character
11:14 - Not all gear is created equal
13:10 - Queue up for EVERYTHING at once
14:18 - There are some chill farms available

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Did the WINNER of the Pro Tour & $50K actually CHEAT? - MTG Rules - MH3
snippet.description:

snippet.title: History of Clash Royale's Most Hated Card
snippet.description:
The Mega Knight is a card that has not had any major reworks, and has had fewer changes than a typical card I would cover, but the community has drove this card through a painful journey, and after everything it's been through, still nearly appears in nearly a quarter of all ladder decks to this day.

Song List:
Attack on Tarir - Guild Wars 2
Melty Monster Galaxy - Super Mario Galaxy 2
Dreiton - C418
Baroque II - Runescape 3
Wicked Wings (Shrunk 2) - Gareth Coker
Auric Wilds - Guild Wars 2
Ruin Tower - Chrono Cross
Over the Shiverpeaks - Guild Wars
Windows XP Tour Track
Alpha - C418

snippet.title: I Made the World's Fastest Farms in Minecraft!
snippet.description:
🕹️ Get a browser that’s literally better at everything: https://operagx.gg/Wunba Sponsored by Opera GX!
▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬
I have plans to build one of the largest mega structures humanity has ever seen, except it requires 580,000 blocks. Today we built 3 of the farms required to collect the materials for that and at the same time decorate those farms by building an EPIC oil rig!

This video took me about 350 hours to create. I originally finished the video and was literally exporting it when the hard drive with all my footage corrupted and it was LOST! I sent the drive to a company that tried to get me to pay $4,500 to repair it and despite that massive cost they literally could not. Thank the lord I didn’t have to pay for it. From there, I spent about 50 hours re-recording and editing the ENTIRE video to get this to you guys! If you notice any creative mode shots or weird inconsistencies please know that this entire video was streamed live as proof, but the footage that actually made it into the video was re-recorded.

Also yes, for every subscriber this video gets I will run 10ft to train for a marathon!
▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬

snippet.title: I Made the World’s Largest Map in Minecraft…
snippet.description:
I attempted to beat the world record for the largest map room in hardcore Minecraft!
▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬
This video was a blast to make! I spent nearly 150 hours with recording and editing to produce it! There was even a time when I accidentally deleted all of the footage and thought I needed to scrap it! That is why I am so proud to present the largest ever map room made fully in hardcore Minecraft to you!

There are about 7,900 maps here in case you were curious.

Thank you @ianxofour for the obsidian farm design! - https://www.youtube.com/user/ianxofour
▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬
Sorting process (for maps)

I didn't want to cover it within the video because it was lengthy to explain, but here is how I sorted the maps to make the room. First of all, I would put about 16 shulker empty boxes inside of my ender chest. From there, I would find the location to start mapping and then put the amount of maps I needed to go in that specific direction into my hotbar. That way I would not need to count the entire time. Whenever the hotbar got full, I would put the maps into the inventory. And whenever that got full, I would put the inventory into shulkers. From there, I would repeat the process. I also had to mentally keep track of my location within the world, plus where the next row of maps would be. This entire process was mentally taxing, but effective in making a circlular map room!
▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬

snippet.title: Five Nights At Freddy's - Twisted Movie
snippet.description:
Finally a Long-awaited Five Nights at Freddy's Twisted Movie is here! 🎥 Are you ready to get spooked?

FNAF: Twisted Movie is your best pick for a spooky movie night 🎥

► Disclaimer - This movie is just a fan - made adaptation of the Five Nights At Freddy's video game and therefore has no connections to the official Five Nights at Freddys Movie 2023
adaptation made by Blumhouse.

☆ Make sure to Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCMBNTj0G84ipsjPzRkK3KDw?sub_confirmation=1

☆ This channel is being run by only one person, so if you like this channel and want to support it, head on to Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/Secret4Studio
Or become a Youtube member: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCMBNTj0G84ipsjPzRkK3KDw/join
☆ One-time donations: paypal.me/secret4studio

☆ For business inquiries: secret4studious@gmail.com

Five Nights at Freddy's: The Twisted Ones deliver the final and most emotional chapter about Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria, Animatronics past, William Afton's plans and shows the outcome of the never ending fight between forces of good and evil. 

Chapters:
Hunted Soul [0:26]
Defending Your Family [07:01]
Sad Truth [16:33]
The Memory Remains [23:07]
Point of No Return [27:21]
Goodbye Stranger [29:10]
Twisted Duo [34:18]
In the Beginning [38:00]
Last Chapter: [44:48]
-----------------------------------------

☆ Also, there are Five Nights at Freddy's Web Series, that expand the story told by Secret4Studio.

snippet.title: The Finals Season 3 is CRAZY! [Livestream]
snippet.description:
The latest Season of The Finals has released - so I wanted to play it LIVE with you all and see how it stacks up! The Finals on Playstation 5 is a different FPS to PC and Xbox, so is The Finals the best FPS available at the moment?
--------------------------------------------------------
My Discord: https://discord.gg/F6tUE7Tb6t
Twitter:  https://twitter.com/itsnortymorty
--------------------------------------------------------
🗣️Stream Commands below (more to be added):🗣️
!like
!video
!qotd
!dice
!discord
!lurk
!car
!schedule
!specs
--------------------------------------------------------------
🖥️ Setup 🖥️
Operating System - Windows 10 Professional 64-bit
CPU - Intel i5 10600k
GPU - 6GB NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2060 Super
RAM - 32.0GB Corsair Vengeance @ 3200Mhz
Headset - Razer Nari Essential Wireless Gaming 
Mouse - Razer Mamba Elite 
Keyboard - Razer Blackwidow Tournament Edition
Monitor - AOC 24G2W1G4 24" 144hz 
Microphone - Shure MV7
Webcam - Razer Kiyo Pro + Live Webcam
-------------------------------------------------------------
Game synopsis: 
The Finals, stylized in all caps as THE FINALS, is a free-to-play first-person shooter, developed and published by Nexon subsidiary Embark Studios. The game focuses on team-based matches on maps with a destructible environment, where players are encouraged to use the dynamic environment to their advantage

#thefinals #thefinalsgame #embarkstudios #thefinalsgameplay

localized.title: i played persona 5 royal for the first time and... [part 3]
localized.description:
howdy hey! here it is, the beginning of the man the myth the legend Yusuke Kitagawa. rocky beginnings but will i come to love him? who's to say mwhahah 
as you can tell, i still cannot edit an entire palace into one video, but here's the mid point/intro into Madarame!! i really loved this part of the game, and it was definitely where i first started to truuuly fall in love with the game, so i hope you also enjoy this video. i am not yet finished with the game (as of 10/04/22), and am playing it on twitch if you ever want to watch! the full playthrough is also available on the VOD youtube, if you want to watch everything and not just highlights :) 

as for content warnings, there's still a lot of discussion of heavy topics: content includes abuse, child abuse, and generally heavy and dark topics, so just look out for yourself! :)

"It's Going Down Now" is the player advantage battle theme in Persona 3 Reload. The song is sung by Lotus Juice and Azumi Takahashi, with lyrics by Lotus Juice. snippet.title: Persona 5 Strikers / Scramble - High Energy Mix [No Gaps]
snippet.description:
Gapless mix of high energy P5S OST songs! Track list in description. Don't forget to like, subscribe and hit the bell :) 

TRACKLIST:
0:00 - You Are Stronger
4:08 - Perturbation
5:04 - Daredevil
9:39 - Last Surprise (Strikers version)
13:31 - Counter Strike
18:35 - Rivers In The Desert (Strikers version)
23:45 - Keeper Of Lust (Strikers Version)
27:22 - Blooming Villain (Strikers Version)

I've always done covers but this time I wanted to do just a simple mix of songs that I'd personally listen to while coding or working out, so here it is! Of course, all credit goes to the original composers of the songs. This video will never be monetized :) 

Please let me know whether you like this in the comments, and if you do I can make some more! 

Also, am I the first to use a Strikers image instead of Scramble? I'm super hyped for the western release and even got the deluxe preorder :D

snippet.title: Café Leblanc | Coffee Shop Ambience: Smooth Jazz Persona Music & Rain to Study, Relax, & Sleep
snippet.description:
Welcome to Café Leblanc! Here you'll find a relaxing coffee shop ambience playing your favorite smooth jazz Persona music perfect for studying, relaxation, and sleep. It's a rainy autumn night in Tokyo. Smell the rich aroma of coffee and listen to the soothing sounds of heavy rain, smooth jazz, and ambient coffee shop chatter. You can overhear the soft conversations of customers along with the gentle jingles of dishes. This dimly lit late night café ASMR ambience is perfect for enhanced focus for work, reading, studying, relaxation, meditation and sleeping. This coffee shop is open for ~1 hour, but you can find the 8 hours looped version on my Patreon!

Click the 🔔 bell to stay updated on all my videos!

⌚ 8-hour looped version HERE ▸ https://www.patreon.com/posts/loop-cafe-88113498
💻 Live wallpaper version HERE ▸ https://www.patreon.com/posts/live-wallpaper-69418020
🌆 Check out my other ambiences HERE ▸ https://bit.ly/3Bc9QZ0
💖 Support me on Patreon HERE ▸ https://www.patreon.com/AmbienceAcademy
💙 Follow me on Twitter HERE ▸ https://twitter.com/NamelessNotes_
🌀 Join our Discord server HERE ▸ https://discord.gg/W2CaNxCDu7

Hey everyone! Welcome to the first upload of the channel! For those unaware, this is the second channel of NAMELESS NOTES. Previously, NAMELESS NOTES was a channel that posted piano covers and ambience videos. However, since YouTube has decided to demonetize ambience videos, I have decided to move all the ambience videos to a separate channel. This channel is NOT being monetized so if you want to see more ambience videos like this one, please consider supporting us on Patreon!

The visuals have been enhanced for this reupload, but I have left the audio untouched. No one has ever commented on this before, but if you listen closely, you can hear the Phantom Thieves studying for their exams in the background!

Until next time ✌,
Ambience Academy

In this video, we invite you to discover the secrets of deep work mastery and explore practical techniques to transcend distractions and enter a state of optimal productivity. Our expertly crafted instrumental tracks are specifically designed to enhance your concentration and elevate your workflow. The harmonious blend of soothing melodies, mesmerizing rhythms, and ambient textures will create a harmonious soundscape that resonates with your desire for deep focus.

Here are some valuable tips to help you quickly enter a state of heightened productivity when listening to our music:

💡 Let the Music Guide You: Allow the captivating melodies and rhythmic beats of our specially curated tracks to guide your focus and amplify your workflow. Let the music become your companion on this profound journey of deep work.

💡 Cultivate Mindful Presence: Prioritize mindful breathing exercises to anchor yourself in the present moment. Take slow, deep breaths, allowing the rhythm of your breath to calm your mind, increase clarity, and enhance your productivity.

💡 Nourish a Growth Mindset: Embrace challenges as opportunities for growth and transformation. Cultivate a mindset that sees setbacks as stepping stones to success, fostering a sense of curiosity, resilience, and continuous improvement.

💡 Embrace Strategic Rest and Rejuvenation: Incorporate strategic breaks into your work routine to recharge and revitalize your mind. Use these intervals to stretch, hydrate, and engage in activities that promote relaxation and spark creative inspiration.

Embark on this profound journey into the depths of focus and productivity. Let the synergy of soul-stirring music and expert guidance propel you towards extraordinary results. snippet.title: 🎧Deep Work Music 24/7 — Concentration Mix for Programming, Coding
snippet.description:
This livestream with a carefully curated mix of tracks is designed specifically to help you focus on programming and coding. Dark and cyber electronic music radio in genres like chillstep and future garage will create the perfect background for working on complex projects or completing routine tasks. Thanks to the futuristic atmosphere of this musical accompaniment, you will be able to immerse yourself in the creative process with special depth and inspiration. These tracks will help you maintain a high level of concentration and productivity to achieve maximum results. Discover new horizons of efficiency with our specially curated musical accompaniment. 

🎯Tips for Deep Focus and Concentration:
1. Movement Meditation: Try practicing movement meditation, such as yoga, tai chi, or walking in a natural environment. This will help clear your mind, improve focus, and reduce stress levels.
2. Polyphasic Sleep: Explore polyphasic sleep methods, which involve taking short periods of sleep throughout the day to enhance your concentration and productivity. Some people find that it allows them to reduce overall sleep time and remain more alert during the day.
3. Color Therapy: Use colors to manage your mood and energy levels. For example, different shades of blue and green can promote calmness and focus, while bright colors like orange or red can stimulate activity and energy.
4. Nature Contemplation Practice: Spend time outdoors, immersing yourself in the natural beauty and sounds of the environment. This can help calm your mind, reduce stress, and increase concentration.
5. Music therapy with our Chill Music Lab playlists: Listen to our playlists or radio, which include relaxing and focusing tracks. Such music can help improve concentration and create a calm working atmosphere for your goals.
